Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "nula" in different forms and positions, with translations in English in parentheses:

1. Danas je temperatura nula stepeni. (*nula* stepeni = zero degrees) (Today the temperature is zero degrees.)
2. Nismo postigli nijedan gol, nula poena. (nula poena = zero points) (We didn't score any goals, zero points.)
3. Učenik je napisao nulu umesto jedinice. (napisao je *nulu* = wrote zero) (The student wrote zero instead of one.)
4. Novi sistem ima nultu toleranciju na greške. (*nultu* toleranciju = zero tolerance) (The new system has zero tolerance for errors.)
5. Zbirka sadrži nula umesto deset knjiga. (sadrži *nula* umesto deset = contains zero instead of ten) (The collection contains zero books instead of ten.)
6. Ovo je nula-sumna igra, jedan igrač gubi onoliko koliko drugi dobija. (nula-sumna igra = zero-sum game) (This is a zero-sum game, one player loses as much as the other one gains.)
7. Kompanija je prošlog meseca zabeležila nulu prihoda. (zabeležila *nulu* prihoda = recorded zero revenue) (The company recorded zero revenue last month.)
8. Upotrebila je nulastični zavoj za ranu. (*nulastični* zavoj = zero-stretch bandage) (She used a zero-stretch bandage for the wound.)
9. Na semaforu su se upalila dva zelena svetla i jedno crveno, nula žutih. (nula *žutih* = zero yellow) (Two green lights and one red light came on the traffic light, zero yellow.)
10. Konobar je pitao da li želite nulu ili dve kockice leda u piću. (*nulu* ili dve kockice leda = zero or two ice cubes) (The waiter asked if you want zero or two ice cubes in your drink.)